<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-06-17T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-06-17T06:00:00-05:00" n="133" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d133">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">865.3311/73: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-06-17T12:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">June 17,
                                        1927—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received June 17—9:05
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>82. Have addressed letter to Premier Mussolini today extending
                            congratulations in the name of the President and the people of the
                            United States on De Pinedo’s return from his air voyage.<note n="4" xml:id="d133fn4">Commander De Pinedo had continued his flight in
                                another plane sent from Italy.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>